items.name: Diaper Flash Under Skirt v0.5 - Realistic ABDL
items.description:
A LORA for making ladies lift their skirt and flash their diaper.

If you like my work you can tip me through Comiss.io.

Another work in progress LORA here, which is frustratingly close to being good. The skirt lifting pose is there, but hands are not always good, and the diapers don't quite look real yet, but at least it's something you can play with.

Polite notice: This LORA only depicts adults doing consensual adult things, and fully complies with the TOS at CivitAI.

There are a number of triggers - The key one is DiaperSkirtLift but you should always tell it if you want a skirt or dress. This LORA also includes posing directions, with full body photo being very helpful to get a proper portrait, mid shot being more zoomed in and (in theory) not including the face and close up being just on the diaper region. You can prompt for standing, and generally you can for sitting and kneeling. I also strongly advise you to add disposable to the prompt, so that you can adjust the diaperyness. Set the LORA to about 0.8 strength to start with, and the CFG to about 3, and then play with both of those depending what results you get.

There are a number of other triggers that were supposed to work, but which don't at the moment. I had intended to let you prompt for pullup but there weren't many in the dataset, and the diaper aspect is quite weak in the LORA overall. You were also supposed to be able to prompt for DiaperPeek for when you just see a peek without her lifting the skirt up, but that does not work very well.

There are issues with this LORA:

Firstly; it hasn't perfectly learned how to "lift". Sometimes it draws skirts/dresses that pull apart at the front like a coat, sometimes it draws them with a cutout at the front, sometimes the skirt is so short there isn't much point lifting it up. It also does not fully understand that the underside of a skirt is normally the same colour as the outside, so it draws contrasting linings that could possibly exist but are certainly not common.

Second; it tends to draw ladies with big chins who look a bit like former Dr Who, Matt Smith. This is unfortunate, and you need to prompt around it. Even when you get it solved it will lead to a lot of very similar looking ladies. It also sometimes gives them glasses.

Third, this version doesn't understand stockings and pleases itself whether it adds them or not. It draws them quite well, but it can be frustrating.

Fourth, the diapers it draws are kinda crappy. Sometimes they look alright, sometimes they look like big white granny panties. It's all about lora strength vs CFG and you just have to fiddle with it. You can use my Tena LORA to help out, but you have to be veeeery careful how you dial that in (like, strength 0.2).

Lastly, remember that SD has issues with drawing hands and fingers. Since holding the skirt is a big part of this, it can ruin a lot of pictures. The LORA is actually not too bad for that, but your eye is going to go there and you will see many shadows and weird double exposures.

The LORA also seems to prefer drawing outdoor scenes, and then bedroom scenes, which is understandable enough, but in both cases those backgrounds can come out quite samey. Indoors it seems to like drawing cluttered rooms too, which looks quite authentic but it does show that the LORA isn't as transparent as I would like.

items.name: Satele Shan (Star Wars the Old Republic) LoRA
items.description:
The Jedi Order's grand master Satele Shan from Star Wars the Old Republic (Swtor) by Bioware. Works best on 0.8-1.0. Training done on NAI.

Trigger: "SateleShan, braid, twin braids, hair tubes" always needed, for consistency add "blue eyes".

Suggestions:

  • Main outfit: "SateleShan, armor, belt, gloves" it works quite well and should not need much of a push as the data was only or her in outfit.

  • The outfit does bleed into other clothes due to lack of data with other outfits.

  • Adding more descriptors or putting things into Negative prompt can help get other clothes working better than they already do.

A fun request from previous LoRA's comments and a nicer more chill project compared to recent characters. I hope you all enjoy.

Feedback and reviews are always appreciated.

items.description:
This LoRA has been trained after carefully selecting 79 images, most of them screenshots from Episode VII movie. All photos have been enhanced to make the most of them.

When downloading model and testing it, try to copy any of the prompts I have used, and make some variations in order to get other images you prefer. Have fun!

LoRA weights should be between 1.1 and 1.4 in my experience (but you're free to test)

For portraits you can use 896 x 1152, 768 x 1344, 832 x 1216, 640 x 1536 or even 768x1024 resolutions.

I don't ask for anything but any respectful constructive review (after having tested the model) would be highly appreciated or at least press Like if you're happy with results after trying it out! Thanks in advance and enjoy it!

items.name: Lucy - Project QT
items.description:
Good day to my 62 fabulous followers, I am back with with good and bad news. First the good news, I successfully reinstalled my linux and windows installation. The bad news is now for some reason my dedicated GPU doesnt want to register as a usable GPU so now im using my CPU to generate the images which is insanely slow (~10s/it vs 2.4s/it) so testing new loras is going to be a hassle until I can find a work around. We also hit 1.5k downloads and more than 400 hearts which is bonkers. Thank you everyone.

Anyways I decided to train one of my low key favorite girls today, which is Lucy! Idk if anyone else likes her but that doesnt matter now since I trained it already. I used my patented© ultra-high-quality tagging technique where I try to bake in more prominent features but still keep her customizable. I also used MeinaHentai to train the lora on. To prompt her I would recommend the following: lucy, white shirt, large breasts, apron/naked apron, skirt, bow, thighhighs, high heels, thick thighs.

With all that out the way, I got 4 girls I have in mind to make next and I just want to see which one you guys would want the most. The list is as follows:

  • Una

  • Geneva

  • Elva

  • Margaret.

Yeah thats it for now. I honestly think think civit should add polls, it would be very helpful tbh but oh well. If you liked the lora make sure to leave a review or post your pics since im always keen to see your generations, and make sure to follow if you like the content I make 😄.

items.name: Kentaro Miura (Berserk) - Artist Style
items.description:
If you enjoyed this model, why don't you check out my other works? I put a lot of effort into correctly recreating artist styles and making the occasional character LoRA.

I am once again open for suggestions for other styles, SFW and NSFW.

You can always drop model suggestions in the comments, both for styles that are missing on civit or those that are outdated.

This model was trained using the collab/guide by holostrawberry [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free - colabs | Stable Diffusion Other | Civitai

About the artist:

At this point who doesn't know this iconic series...

If you somehow missed it, Berserk is one of the most influential (dark) fantasy manga of our time. Sadly, Miura wasn't able to finish it himself but nevertheless it continues, although in a shortened form.

Weights & Prompts

The only necessary prompt is:

kentaro_miura_berserk

Try using

monochrome, greyscale,  nib pen (medium)

for scenery in particular.

Use a weight of 0.8-1.0, adjust to taste and depending on your checkpoint.

As usual I have included an XYZ plot for reference.

As I exclusively trained with monochrome manga panels it will prefer black and white image generation. This doesn't prevent you from creating colorful images but hampers the flexibility. You can also expect a certain drop in the accuracy of the model when forcing colors.

I have also never seen a model interact so weirdly with character LoRA before. I recommend experimenting a lot with the weights for those.

Please leave a review if you enjoyed this model or have problems with it. This helps me with improving future models and finetuning them in general. Give it a try and throw some images down below!

items.name: kwFemale SDXL
items.description:
Thanks for the interest in this LoRA creation. This project has been conducted in Stable Diffusion 1.5 since March 2023.The objective of this project is to create an ideal training data set for LoRA. After the launching of SDXL, the scope of this research was expanded to this new version.

The face of the researcher was taken as reference in order to create the training set. 15 photos were taken purposely for AI training only. These 15 photos contain different angles of face and shoulder to fulfill the AI training requirement.

After trying different combinations of settings, an optimal adjustment was found.

Comparison of Dim256, Dim128, and no LoRA respectively.

*********************************************************

Here is the log for different version.

Beta1: First trying with suggested learning rate 4e-7, resolution 1024x1024, dimension 256, alpha 256, optimizer: Adafactor. Result unsatisfied.

Beta2: Change the learning rate in Beta1 to 0.0004. Result unsatisfied.

Beta3: Reduce the learning rate in Beta2 to 0.0001, increase the steps of each photo to 100. Result unsatisfied.

Beta4: Replace the resolution in Beta3 to 2048x2048, reduce the steps of each photo to 20. Result unsatisfied.

Beta5: Increase the steps of each photo to 100 in Beta4. Result unsatisfied.

Beta6: Applying learning rate 0.0004, resolution 1024x1024, 20 steps of each photo, alpha 1. Result unsatisfied.

Beta7: Reduce learning rate to 0.0001, resolution 960x960, alpha 256. Result unsatisfied.

Beta8: Reduce learning rate to 0.00001, resolution 1024x1024, 20 steps of each photo. Result unsatisfied.

Beta9: Reduce learning rate to 0.000005. Result unsatisfied.

Beta10: Reduce resolution 512x512, 40 steps of each photo. Result unsatisfied

Beta11: Using two subset of resolutions 512x512 and 1024x1024, 40 steps of each photo. Set max resolution to 512x512, dimension 128, alpha 128. Result unsatisfied.

Beta12: Set Max resolution to 1024x1024, dimension 64, alpha 64. Result unsatisfied.

Beta13: Replace optimizer to prodigy, learning rate 1, dimension 128, alpha 128. Result unsatisfied

Beta14: Replace optimizer to adamW8bits, learning rate 0.0001, 20 steps, dimension 256, alpha 256. Result satisfied.

Beta15: Reduce the learning rate to 0.000005. Result satisfied. Uploaded to Civitai as version 1. Marked as miletone.

Beta16: Increase the learning rate to 0.00001, no better results.

Beta17: Reduce the learning rate to 0.000005, dimension 128, alpha 128. Applying Text Encoder learning rate to 0.000005, Unet learning rate to 0.00001. No better results.

Beta18: Removed Text Encoder learning rate and Unet learning rate. No better results.

Beta19: Increased learning rate to 0.0001, resolution 512x512 only, 80 steps, dimension 256, alpha 256, clip skip 2. No better results.

Beta20: Reduced learning rate to 0.00001. No better results.

Beta21: Increased resolution to 960x960. No better results.

Beta22: Reduced learning rate to 0.000001, resolution 1024x1024, 100 steps. No better results.

Beta23: Reduced learning rate to 0.0000004, 400 steps. No better results.

Beta24: Reduced steps to 200, dimension 64, alpha 64, skip clip 1. No better results.

Beta25: Increased learning rate to 0.00001, 30 steps, dimension 256, alpha 256. Result satisfying. Marked as second milestone.

Beta26: Reduced learning rate to 0.000005, 20 steps, No better results.

Beta27: Increased learning rate to 0.00001, 30 steps, dimension 64, alpha 64. Result satisfying.

Beta28: Replace new training data set. Uploaded to Civitai as Dim64 version.

Beta29: Increased dimension to 256, alpha 256. No better results.

Beta30: Increased resolution to 1536x1536. No better results

Beta31: Increased resolution to 2048x2048. No better results

Beta32: Changed resolution to 1536x2048. No better results

Beta33: Reduced resolution to 1280x1280, 40 steps. No better results

Beta34: Changed resolution to 1024x1536, 30 steps, new set of the training data. No better results.

Beta35: Changed resolution to 1024x1280. No better results.

Beta36: Changed resolution to 1024x1024. No better results.

Beta37: Changed resolution to 1024x1024, 50 steps. No better results.

*********************************************************

Since it is ongoing project, your valuable feedback is important, in order to bring this project to the next level.

items.name: AstreaPixie Radiance Hentai
items.description:
First release of Radiance merged with MeinaHentaiV4. It still aims at anime feeling with vibrant color, which will stay on the Radiance series. Prompting is hard as it is not a merge model like you are used to see. Not recommended for beginners.

After dowloading rename the file to : AstreaPixie_RadianceHentai_v1.6pruned

This is because Civitai limits model name to 20 characters

Recommended Settings

- Clip skip: 2
- CFG scale: 7
- Sampler: Euler, Euler A, DPM++ SDE and DPM++ 2m Karras
- Sampling Steps : 20-30
- Upscaler (Hires. fix): 4x_NMKD-Superscale-SP_178000_G  
- Hires steps: 10-15  Denoising strength: 0.4  Upscale by: 1.5+

Using Adetailer

- Main UI > Extensions > Install from URL
    This mainly fixes problems with faces and eyes. Do not use for hands.
    This can be enable and nothing else to do to works.

Why is my results different from yours?

  • Enable quantization in K samplers in your settings

  • Keep your prompts simple and correct

    • Tag auto complete extension to help you with your tags

    • Neg embedding have a great impact on the output of a model

    • Depending on the one you are using, results will be different.

    • I mainly use fitCorder embeddings for negative :)

You can support me on Ko-Fi and Patreon

items.name: Twink's Anatomy
items.description:
This model has serious femboy tendencies. Enjoy. (This is a SFW LORA, though.)

The images posted came straight directly from SDXL generation. In my workflow, I do take them to photoshop and add a touch of sharpen. Also, the I did not think the use of SDXL refiner needed although, if you use a higher denoising strength, might be interesting to apply the LORA also to the refiner. In lower denoising strengths I see no need to use it.

This model might be considered under-trained, but I do like it the way it is. It's lot more subtle than creating a caracter or hardcoding anything more objective into it. It focus on presenting the model with a body type (of a twink) and blurring a bit the limits of what is masculine and feminine. Sometimes the legs get a bit too long, though.

It came from the frustration of generating some images back in SD1.5/2.1 and having the problem that the boys would get super muscular and masculine or become girls with breasts and everything. I wanted something in between. So I started baking the idea of creating a LORA to achieve it but then XL got launched. It's actually a bit easier to get good results with XL in this matter, but some things are still very hard coded into the models making other things difficult. This LORA is a study of model creation, so things might need improvement. I'm open for tips, opinions and advice.

❤️ - Ko-fi ❤️ Where creators get support from fans through donations, memberships, shop sales, and more! The original 'Buy Me a Coffee Page.;https://ko-fi.com/steverogers080863

I do not support any indecent images generated of all persons in this model, I do not support selling generated images of persons in this model. please refrain from what they have been posting online.

All persons in this model are 21+ and not a minor, please DO NOT post explicit nudity, suggestive, or pornographic content online using this model. Refer to CivitAi TOS for more details.

===

Request or Suggestion Rule:

  1. No request for a minor!

  2. The requested should have public data (not private)

  3. Should have more than 30 good-quality images

  4. Since all requests or suggestions are free, I will still need to like your request, otherwise its a work not a hobby for me.

  5. Be a decent human being and leave a review if your request is up It takes you only 5 mins while it takes me hours, electricity, and effort to do your requests.

  6. If you don't get what you want, do not review the bomb, there could be other creators' models or Lora that can get better results than mine, use theirs instead, and leave a good review on them too, support any other creators for their complex works!

NOTE: I will keep updating more actresses in versions update

===

Usage Guide

--

A. Lora Weight

  • 0.1 ~ 0.4 -- is to combine multiple faces or features, or if you experience overbaking

  • 0.5 ~ 0.7 -- is a balanced weight to get still accurate features but with more flexibility

  • 0.8 ~ 1.0 -- is to create an accurate representation of the features.

B. CFG Scale

  • A lower CFG Scale means AI gets more creative and less overbaking problems.

  • A higher CFG Scale means results get very accurate with training sets and are more prone to overbaking problems.

  • Dynamic CFG Threshold, using this method allows you to bump up quality and achieve photorealistic quickly, but with lycoris, I found out recently that this method actually lowers the success rate, so only use it when you are composing with a Lora / model that works fine with this method.

C. Sampling Steps, High Res Fix & Upscaling

  • I like sampling steps at 50, with high res steps at 20, or 1/2 of the sampling steps.

  • I find that 2M Karras works better and faster than SDE Karras. with ERSGAN 4x+ method + ERSGAN 4x for Upscaling. This method actually gives quite good results without being too sharp or too plasticky

  • Upscaling - GPFGAN @0.25, Codeformer @0.3 & Codeformer Weight @0.15 seems to yield superior results.

Enjoy.

Scarlett Johansson is an American actress of Danish descent who probably doesn't need my usual introduction. :P

120-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Do you have a specific idea for a TI in mind? Visit my website and let me know.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (scj0_jg:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

items.name: POV Cowgirl & Breast Grab // Concept Pose LoRA
items.description:
Sample images were generated with clip skip 2, DPM++ 2S a Karras. Weight 0.8 is usually best.

Anime models typically work well with cowgirl position, but SD in general is bad with hands and hand poses. For my first ever public LoRA, I decided to fix this problem in the case of one particularly based pose. Don't think about what this says about me.

The model is fairly flexible and, while there is the usual element of lottery, it is fairly consistent in my experience. It does need good prompting, and the specific tags you need to use will probably vary by base model. The provided tags are a good starting point.

Feedback would be greatly appreciated since I am new :)

items.name: style-nebula
items.description: This textual inversion can make some very interesting results when added to the end of a prompt by saying "in the style of style-nebula" I made it using one image using the dreamartist extension in automatic 1111. I made it so I could make more cosmic and spacelike images. At first I was skeptical of dreamartist because it was just one image but I was impressed by this. I've also found that using style-nebula at the beginning of the prompt can create some intriguing results too.
